From: nix-wasm <eric@codebutler.com>
Date: Tue, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] virtio_wasm: add VW_DEV_BLK (virtio-blk, device index 3)

Register a virtio-blk device on the wasm virtio transport as device
index 3 (VW_DEV_BLK), using the standard VIRTIO_ID_BLOCK (2) virtio
device id.  This wires the kernel's CONFIG_VIRTIO_BLK driver into the
host-callback transport, enabling a read-only squashfs image to be
served to the guest over a virtio-blk device rather than 9P JSON.

The registration is guarded by IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_VIRTIO_BLK) so the
enum index and init call are a no-op when the driver is absent.

Part of the #43 squashfs-over-virtio-blk spike (Task 1).
---
 drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c b/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
index 2e5dbc305..b47e06ce7 100644
--- a/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
+++ b/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
@@ -362,6 +362,9 @@ enum {
 #endif
 #ifdef CONFIG_VIRTIO_NET
 	VW_DEV_NET,		/* virtio-net NIC (stock drivers/net/virtio_net.c) */
+#endif
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_VIRTIO_BLK)
+	VW_DEV_BLK,		/* virtio-blk block device (squashfs /nix image) */
 #endif
 	VW_DEV_COUNT,
 };
@@ -385,6 +388,13 @@ static int __init virtio_wasm_transport_init(void)
 	if (IS_ERR(vw))
 		return PTR_ERR(vw);
 #endif
+
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_VIRTIO_BLK)
+	vw = virtio_wasm_register(VW_DEV_BLK, VIRTIO_ID_BLOCK);
+	if (IS_ERR(vw))
+		pr_warn("virtio_wasm: blk register failed: %ld\n", PTR_ERR(vw));
+#endif
+
 	return 0;
 }

